he system tool to open previews).\n\nAvailable operations:\n\n- get_info: Get high-level metadata about preview content including path, content type, and block count\n- search: Search for text in preview content. Returns matches with surrounding context. Supports case-sensitive search, limiting results, and regular expression matching\n- scroll_to: Scroll preview to a specific content position. Must provide block_index (0-based). Optional section_index and text_position for finer control within a section. Optional position parameter controls where in viewport: 'top', 'center' (default), or 'bottom'", 'parameters': {'type': 'object', 'properties': {'operation': {'type': 'string', 'description': 'Preview operation to perform', 'enum': ['get_info', 'search', 'scroll_to']}, 'tab_id': {'type': 'string', 'description': 'GUID of the preview tab to operate on'}, 'search_text': {'type': 'string', 'description': 'Text to search for (for search operation)'}, 'case_sensitive': {'type': 'boolean', 'description': 'Whether search should be case-sensitive'}, 'regexp': {'type': 'boolean', 'description': 'Whether to treat search_text as a regular expression (for search operation)'}, 'max_results': {'type': 'integer', 'description': 'Maximum number of search results to return'}, 'block_index': {'type': 'integer', 'description': 'Content block index (0-based) for scroll_to operation'}, 'section_index': {'type': 'integer', 'description': 'Section index within content block (0-based) for scroll_to operation'}, 'text_position': {'type': 'integer', 'description': 'Text position within section (0-based) for scroll_to operation'}, 'position': {'type': 'string', 'description': "Viewport position for scrolling: 'top', 'center', or 'bottom'"}}, 'required': ['operation', 'tab_id']}}}, {'type': 'function', 'function': {'name': 'help', 'description': 'Get detailed documentation for AI tools and their operations. Use this when you need to understand what a tool can do, how it behaves, its tool para